The paper deals with information theoretic channels in TDD MU-MIMO systems, which involves communication theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The analysis is based on Multiport Communication Theory, which is a system-level theory for modeling and analyzing complex communication systems (cs.SY). The paper also considers the impact of mutual coupling between antenna elements, which is a topic in antenna theory (cs.MM) and applied electromagnetics (cs.AR).
